text: Coagh is a village in Northern Ireland, in the United Kingdom. ==Population facts== On 29 April 2001 the United Kingdom government had a census and found that there were 545 people living in Coagh. They also found that: * 20.9% of people in Coagh were under 16 years old and 20.4% were over 60 years old * 48.3% were male and 51.7% were female * 26.4% were from a Roman Catholic background and 72.8% were from a Protestant background * 2.3% of people aged 16â€“74 had no job. ==References== Category:Villages in Northern Ireland
